  <chapter id="introduction">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
    The <application>Ubuntu Software Store</application> allows you to 
    manage applications with a click of a button. You can browse through 
    the categories to find applications or search through all of the 
    applications using the search box. 
    </para> 
  </chapter> 
  
  <chapter id="getting-started">
    <title>Getting Started</title>
    <sect1 id="starting-software-store">
        <title>Starting The Ubuntu Software Store</title>
        <para>
            There are two ways to start the Ubuntu Software Store:
        </para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                 From the main menu, select 
                 <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>System</guimenu>
                    <guisubmenu>Administration</guisubmenu>
                    <guimenuitem>Ubuntu Software Store</guimenuitem>
                 </menuchoice>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
            To run the Software Store from the command line, run:
                <programlisting>software-store pkgname</programlisting>
                <i>Where pkgname is an (optional) name of a package to open the Software Store at.</i>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="main-window">
        <title>Main Window</title>
        <para>
        When you start the Ubuntu Software Store, the following window is displayed.
        </para>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="./figures/placeholder.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
              <caption>
                <para>Ubuntu Software Store main window</para>
              </caption>
            </mediaobject>
          </screenshot>
          <para>The main window of consists of the following:</para>
          <orderedlist>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Menu bar</guilabel> - allows you to perform specific actions, filter the software displayed or look for help.</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Navigation pane</guilabel> - displays the different parts of the Software Store.</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Main Pane</guilabel> - shows the software available from the category chosen from the software catalog column.</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Location bar</guilabel> - indicates where you are in the Software Store.</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Search field</guilabel> - searches for a piece of specific software.</para></listitem>
                    <listitem><para><guilabel>Status bar</guilabel> - displays information relating to what you are currently viewing.</para></listitem>
          </orderedlist>
    </sect1>
  </chapter>
  
    <chapter id="managing-applications">
    <title>Managing Applications</title>
     <sect1 id="searching-applications">
		<title>Searching for applications to manage</title>
		<para>The first thing to do before installing or removing an application using The <application>Ubuntu Software Store</application> is to locate it from the software catalog. To start a search from the software catalog, do the following:</para>
		<procedure>
                <step>
					<para>To manage an installed application, click the <guilabel>Installed Software</guilabel> item from the navigation pane. To manage an application that is not installed yet, click the <guilabel>Get Free Software</guilabel> item from the navigation pane.</para>				
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>(optional) Select a category from the department lobby. This will filter your search to only those pieces of software that are in this category.</para>				
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>Type the name of the application you wish to locate in the search field.</para>				
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>When you find the application you need, click on the arrow beside the name of the application in the Main Pane to see more details.</para>				
				</step>
		</procedure>
		<screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="./figures/placeholder.png" format="PNG"/>
          </imageobject>
          <caption>
            <para>Use the search field to search for applications to manage.</para>
          </caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot>
    </sect1>
